    "body": "It is not clear what the intent of the log4j2 conf under integration tests \r\n```\r\n$ git ls-files 'integration_tests/**/log4j2*'\r\nintegration_tests/src/test/resources/log4j2.properties\r\n```\r\nit would only be included in the test artifact and not the main artifact which we do not use \r\n\r\nEven if we used it it would not work in the situations where the jar is loaded dynamically outside the app classloader. Only in the static classpath configs using extraClassPaths\r\n\r\n\r\nThe only robust option is to pass an absolute file path via extaJavaOptions \r\n\r\n--driver-java-options / spark.executor.extraJavaOptions=\"-Dlog4j2.configurationFile=file:$PWD/integration_tests/src/main/resources/log4j2.properties\" \r\n\r\nbut to deal with xdist the output should use the run_dir with worker id.\r\n\r\n",
